geneVariantDescriptions.description: PAK5 T538N lies within the protein kinase domain of the Pak5 protein (UniProt.org). T538N results in increased activity of Pak5 towards Craf and increased Erk pathway activation in cell culture (PMID: 23836671).

references.title: Targeted genetic dependency screen facilitates identification of actionable mutations in FGFR4, MAP3K9, and PAK5 in lung cancer.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Selumetinib (AZD6244) inhibited viability of non-small cell lung cancer cells harboring PAK5 T538N, along with concurrent BRAF L597V and NRAS Q61K mutations, in culture (PMID: 23836671).

molecularProfile.profileName: BRAF L597V NRAS Q61K PAK5 T538N

references.title: Targeted genetic dependency screen facilitates identification of actionable mutations in FGFR4, MAP3K9, and PAK5 in lung cancer.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, treatment with L779450 inhibited ERK signaling and resulted in decreased viability a non-small cell lung cancer cell line harboring three ERK-pathway activating mutations, BRAF L597V, NRAS Q61K, and PAK5 T538N, in culture (PMID: 23836671).
